  "text": "Cartilage behaves highly visco-elastically in joints. Specifically, peak cartilage deformation is reached much later than peak joint loads. Here, we found that peak cartilage deformations in the dynamic loading experiments were reached at the end of the 15 cyclic contractions, suggesting that cartilage deformation would have been greater than found here had joint loading been applied for longer than 15 contractions. This result is in agreement with other reports [CITATION_1] using cartilage explants where it was found that the number of loading cycles required to achieve a steady-state deformation response in normal bovine articular cartilage was at least 33 cycles.",
